e%20of%20generational%20warfare%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20collage%20of%20different%20generations%2C%20from%20left%20to%20right%2C%20millennials%2C%20boomers%2C%20gen-z.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b996c503c40c001a971882%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGen%20Z%20hates%20boomers%2C%20everyone%20hates%20millennials%2C%20and%20no%20one%20thinks%20about%20Gen%20X.%20Why%20are%20we%20so%20obsessed%20with%20talking%20about%20generations%3F%3Cp%3EChelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20is%20soft%2C%20millennials%20are%20embarrassing%2C%20boomers%20are%20evil%2C%20and%20no%20one%20has%20thought%20about%20Gen%20X%20in%20years.%20Even%20if%20we%20can't%20remember%20exactly%20which%20ages%20define%20each%20cohort%2C%20many%20people%20can%20offer%20up%20these%20generational%20stereotypes%20on%20command.%20These%20supposedly%20profound%20differences%20have%20been%20used%20to%20explain%20shifting%20attitudes%20about%20certain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-pink-gen-z-yellow-very-peri-orchid-flower-generational-colors-2022-1%5C%22%3Ecolors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-fast-food-restaurant-dining-habits-generations-money-spicy-2023-4%5C%22%3Erising%20popularity%20of%20spicy%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20even%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-does-adulthood-begin-adulting-2019-1%5C%22%3Eperceived%20onset%20of%20adulthood%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20while%20generational%20framings%20are%20ubiquitous%2C%20just%20how%20real%20are%20these%20fault%20lines%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20has%20spent%20decades%20conducting%20surveys%20and%20research%20about%20what%20each%20generation%20thinks%2C%20feels%2C%20and%20is%20doing.%20Its%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewtrusts.org%2Fen%2Ftrust%2Farchive%2Fspring-2019%2Fwho-is-generation-z%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estart%20and%20end%20dates%20for%20generations%3C%2Fa%3E%20became%20the%20standard%20for%20news%20publications%2C%20academic%20research%2C%20and%20dinner-table%20arguments.%20But%20late%20this%20spring%2C%20Pew%20announced%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F05%2F22%2Fhow-pew-research-center-will-report-on-generations-moving-forward%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20would%20no%20longer%20use%20generational%20labels%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20millennial%20and%20Gen%20Z%20in%20its%20research.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20Pew%20quietly%20ended%20a%20tradition%20that%20had%20in%20recent%20years%20become%20a%20source%20of%20growing%20frustration%20(and%20heated%20debate)%20in%20social-science%20circles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%2C%20said%20Kim%20Parker%2C%20the%20center's%20director%20of%20social-trends%20research%2C%20is%20that%20what%20we%20call%20a%20generation%20covers%20too%20wide%20of%20a%20time%20span%20to%20offer%20any%20useful%20insight.%20Generations%20span%2015%20to%2018%20years%2C%20Parker%20explained%20to%20me%20in%20an%20email%2C%20making%20it%20challenging%20to%20home%20in%20on%20a%20handful%20of%20attributes%20that%20realistically%20apply%20to%20the%20whole%20group.%20A%2027-year-old%20is%20likely%20to%20experience%20today's%20lightning-fast%20social%20and%20technological%20changes%20differently%20than%20a%2039-year-old%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20though%20both%20are%20considered%20millennials%20under%20Pew's%20definition.%20And%20it%20may%20be%20hard%20to%20generalize%20about%20a%20generation%20whose%20eldest%20members%20were%20already%20in%20the%20workforce%20when%20the%202008%20recession%20hit%20but%20whose%20youngest%20were%20just%20leaving%20elementary%20school.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20account%20for%20this%20%26quot%3Bgreat%20diversity%20of%20thought%2C%20experience%20and%20behavior%20within%20generations%2C%26quot%3B%20Parker%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F05%2F22%2Fhow-pew-research-center-will-report-on-generations-moving-forward%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%20an%20essay%20on%20the%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Pew%20will%20reframe%20generational%20research%20in%20the%20context%20of%20%26quot%3Bage%20cohorts%26quot%3B%3A%20groupings%20of%20people%20who%20were%20born%20in%20a%20particular%20time%20frame%20who%20might%20have%20experienced%20major%20societal%20events%20in%20meaningfully%20similar%20ways.%20%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20it%20could%20be%20a%20group%2Fcohort%20that%20came%20of%20age%20politically%20when%20Obama%20was%20president%2C%20or%20it%20could%20be%20young%20adults%20who%20were%20in%20college%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20or%20we%20could%20group%20people%20by%20birth%20decade%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Pew%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20question%20isn't%20whether%20young%20adults%20today%20are%20different%20from%20middle-aged%20or%20older%20adults%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Parker%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20question%20is%20whether%20young%20adults%20today%20are%20different%20from%20young%20adults%20at%20some%20specific%20point%20in%20the%20past.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPew's%20announcement%20raises%20questions%20about%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20stream%20of%20generational%20content%20we've%20been%20served.%20Is%20there%20really%20a%20cohesive%20Gen%20Z%3F%20Does%20it%20make%20sense%20to%20compare%20millennials%20to%20boomers%3F%20Are%2020-year-olds%20always%20just%2020-year-olds%3F%20At%20its%20core%2C%20Pew's%20decision%20makes%20clear%20that%20generations%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20distinctions%20we%20draw%20between%20them%20%E2%80%94%20are%20simply%20made%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20generations%20are%20fake%2C%20why%20do%20we%20care%20so%20much%20about%20them%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFake%20generations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20probably%20familiar%20with%20each%20generation's%20unique%20flavor%20of%20malcontent.%20Millennials%20(born%20from%201981%20to%201996%2C%20according%20to%20Pew)%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faverage-american-millennial-net-worth-student-loan-debt-savings-habits-2019-6%5C%22%3Elazy%2C%20self-obsessed%2C%20and%20slow%20to%20launch%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Baby%20boomers%20(1946%20to%201964)%20are%20entitled%2C%20selfish%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-greed-ruined-economy-gen-z-millennials-labor-shortage-inflation-2023-3%5C%22%3Ebasically%20the%20root%20of%20all%20societal%20ills%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%20Gen%20Zers%20(1997%20to%202012)%20are%20tech-obsessed%2C%20psychologically%20fragile%2C%20and%20either%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsponsored.chronicle.com%2FGeneration-Z-The-Woke-Generation%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoo%20woke%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spectator.co.uk%2Farticle%2Fwhy-gen-z-is-turning-against-woke-culture%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20woke%20enough%3C%2Fa%3E%20(looks%20like%20the%20jury's%20out%20on%20that%20one).%20And%20Gen%20Xers%20(1965%20to%201980)%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fdavid-gergen-cnn-generation-x_n_627b5928e4b0d7ea4cd40ffc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewho%20cares%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Yawn!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20of%20generations%20was%20born%20roughly%20a%20century%20ago.%20The%20sociologist%20Karl%20Mannheim%20developed%20the%20notion%20of%20discrete%20%26quot%3Bgeneration%20units%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarcuse.faculty.history.ucsb.edu%2Fclasses%2F201%2Farticles%2F27MannheimGenerations.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20his%201928%20essay%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BThe%20Problem%20of%20Generations.%26quot%3B%20When%20a%20group%20of%20people%20experience%20a%20historical%20or%20cultural%20event%20at%20a%20formative%20age%2C%20Mannheim%20argued%2C%20they%20develop%20a%20distinct%20consciousness%20that%20becomes%20a%20part%20of%20their%20shared%20identity.%20In%20a%20New%20Yorker%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2021%2F10%2F18%2Fits-time-to-stop-talking-about-generations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eessay%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%202021%2C%20Louis%20Menand%20linked%20this%20idea%20to%20the%20interwar%20explosion%20in%20high-school%20attendance%20in%20the%20US%3A%20In%201910%2C%20only%2014%25%20of%20Americans%20between%2014%20and%2017%20were%20in%20school%2C%20but%20by%201940%20that%20had%20rocketed%20to%2073%25.%20Menand%20argued%20that%20the%20high-school%20boom%20gave%20rise%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bteenager%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20whole%20new%20social%20category%20and%20marketing%20demographic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThere's%20only%20so%20much%20to%20be%20gleaned%20about%20a%20person%20from%20a%20haphazardly%20drawn%2C%20nearly%20two-decade%20window%20that%20happens%20to%20encompass%20their%20birth%20year.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20idea%20of%20generations%20percolated%20for%20decades%2C%20today's%20intense%20obsession%20with%20age%20cohorts%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20the%201992%20book%20%26quot%3BGenerations.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fosf.io%2Fpreprints%2Fsocarxiv%2Fe2zxr%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Skidmore%20College%20sociologists%20Andrew%20M.%20Lindner%2C%20Sophia%20Stelboum%2C%20and%20Azizul%20Hakim%20say%20the%20book's%20authors%2C%20William%20Strauss%20and%20Neil%20Howe%2C%20drew%20on%20%26quot%3Ba%20long%20lineage%20of%20quasi-scientific%20romantic%20historical%20generational%20thinking%26quot%3B%20to%20help%20popularize%20today's%20generational%20terminology.%20The%20book%20even%20came%20up%20with%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bmillennial.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20the%20release%20of%20Strauss%20and%20Howe's%20influential%20book%2C%20the%20generational%20labels%20of%20'Baby%20Boomer%2C'%20'Gen%20X%2C'%20'Millennials%2C'%20and%20'Gen%20Z'%20have%20appeared%20in%20dozens%20of%20trade%20paperbacks%2C%20thousands%20of%20newspaper%20headlines%2C%20and%20all%20over%20social%20media%2C%26quot%3B%20Lindner%20and%20his%20colleagues%20said.%20%26quot%3BEach%20of%20these%20labels%20is%20associated%20with%20a%20package%20of%20supposed%20psychological%20traits%2C%20behavioral%20patterns%2C%20and%20political%20commitments%20typical%20of%20each%20respective%20generation%20(e.g.%2C%20being%20narcissistic%2C%20parting%20one's%20hair%20in%20the%20middle%2C%20destroying%20the%20global%20economy).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20our%20generation-tinted%20cultural%20lens%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F12%2F10%2Fstyle%2Fwhite-lotus-costumes-portia.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20outfits%3C%2Fa%3E%20worn%20by%20the%20character%20Portia%20on%20the%20second%20season%20of%20the%20HBO%20series%20%26quot%3BThe%20White%20Lotus%26quot%3B%20are%20seen%20not%20just%20as%20the%20sartorial%20missteps%20of%20a%20judgment-challenged%2020-something%20but%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.refinery29.com%2Fen-gb%2Fthe-white-lotus-portia-fashion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20comment%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20how%20an%20entire%20generation's%20sense%20of%20style%20was%20broken%20by%20social%20media.%20The%20consulting%20behemoth%20McKinsey's%20speculation%20on%20the%20future%20of%20work%20focuses%20not%20just%20on%20technological%20developments%20but%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Ffeatured-insights%2Fsustainable-inclusive-growth%2Ffuture-of-america%2Fhow-does-gen-z-see-its-place-in-the-working-world-with-trepidation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkplace%20generation%20gap%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20everyone%20else.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-millennials-birth-fertility-rate-declining-fewer-babies-2022-1%5C%22%3EDeclining%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-millennial-baby-boom-probably-isnt-going-to-happen-2021-12%5C%22%3Ebirth%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Generational.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fscience%2F2021%2F05%2F26%2Fgen-z-millennials-stand-out-for-climate-change-activism-social-media-engagement-with-issue%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClimate%20activism%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Also%20generational.%20The%20list%20goes%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20social%20scientists%20have%20long%20chafed%20at%20the%20idea%20of%20using%20generations%20to%20understand%20our%20changing%20culture%2C%20and%20there%20are%20numerous%20problems%20with%20overdeploying%20the%20generational%20framework.%20For%20one%2C%20there's%20only%20so%20much%20to%20be%20gleaned%20about%20a%20person%20from%20a%20haphazardly%20drawn%2C%20nearly%20two-decade%20window%20that%20happens%20to%20encompass%20their%20birth%20year.%20Generational%20discussions%20also%20tend%20to%20ignore%20critical%20variables%20such%20as%20race%2C%20education%2C%20and%20gender%20%E2%80%94%20as%20Pew%20researchers%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F05%2F22%2F5-things-to-keep-in-mind-when-you-hear-about-gen-z-millennials-boomers-and-other-generations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epointed%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20generational%20stereotypes%20carry%20a%20distinctly%20upper-class%20bias.%20And%20they%20often%20amplify%20points%20of%20perceived%20difference%20instead%20of%20reflecting%20the%20similarities%20between%20groups.%20At%20one%20point%20or%20another%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fnational%2Farchive%2F2013%2F05%2Fme-generation-time%2F315151%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboomers%2C%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20millennials%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F05%2F15%2Fscience%2Fnarcissism-teenagers.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Zers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20all%20been%20branded%20(in%20so%20many%20words)%20as%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20%3C%2Fem%3Eself-absorbed%20sociopaths%20of%20their%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20good%20chunk%20of%20the%20generational%20fascination%20comes%20down%20to%20people's%20interest%20in%20what%20the%20kids%20are%20up%20to.%20But%20even%20then%2C%20polls%20about%20Gen%20Z's%20attitudes%20typically%20leave%20out%20crucial%20context.%20%26quot%3BThe%20issue%20there%20is%20that%20young%20adults%20will%20change%20as%20they%20get%20older%2C%26quot%3B%20Parker%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we%20can't%20really%20assess%20how%20their%20attitudes%20and%20behaviors%20are%20unique%20without%20the%20benefit%20of%20historical%20data.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20see%20whether%20young%20people's%20attitudes%20toward%20work%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20are%20actually%20all%20that%20different%20from%20older%20workers'%20attitudes%2C%20researchers%20would%20need%20data%20on%20young%20people's%20views%20on%20work%20over%20time.%20But%20that%20kind%20of%20historical%20data%20is%20unfortunately%20lacking.%20So%20it's%20hard%2C%20if%20not%20impossible%2C%20to%20compare%20Gen%20Z's%20thoughts%20on%20the%20workplace%20with%20Gen%20X's%20thoughts%20on%20the%20workplace%20when%20they%20were%20the%20same%20age.%20And%20without%20that%20historical%20data%2C%20what%20you're%20really%20comparing%20is%20how%2020-year-olds%20feel%20about%20work%20with%20how%2050-year-olds%20feel%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Kids%20these%20days'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EArtificial%20or%20not%2C%20generational%20tensions%20have%20calcified%20into%20easy%20shorthand%20for%20advertisers%2C%20writers%2C%20and%20consultants.%20Popular%20reporting%20on%20generations%20tends%20to%20fill%20in%20information%20gaps%20with%20generalizations%20that%20flatten%20the%20various%20groups%20into%20catchphrases.%20But%20Philip%20N.%20Cohen%2C%20a%20sociologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Maryland%2C%20College%20Park%2C%20suggests%20this%20troublesome%20reflex%20can't%20necessarily%20be%20chalked%20up%20to%20cynicism%20or%20malice%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%2C%20not%20entirely.%20It%20also%20comes%20from%20a%20real%2C%20compassionate%20human%20desire%20to%20connect%20with%20each%20other.%20Generation%20talk%2C%20he%20said%2C%20can%20help%20people%20scratch%20the%20itch%20of%20understanding%2C%20especially%20during%20periods%20of%20rapid%20social%20and%20technological%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStereotyping%20is%20just%20very%20powerful%2C%20whether%20you%20love%20it%20or%20hate%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Cohen%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20clicking%20on%20an%20article%20about%20generation%20concepts%2C%20it%20may%20be%20because%20you're%20irritated%20or%20cackling%20at%20the%20stereotype%20that's%20being%20portrayed%20in%20the%20headline%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20because%20you're%20trying%20to%20understand%20how%20the%20culture%20is%20changing.%20And%20I%20think%20there's%20a%20great%20impulse%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EWe%20might%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20kids%20these%20days%20are%20different%2C'%20when%20really%20it's%20that%20people%20these%20days%20are%20different%2C%20and%20kids%20are%20kids.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3ECohen%20has%20nonetheless%20been%20among%20the%20most%20vocal%20recent%20critics%20of%20generational%20labeling%20in%20social%20research%20%E2%80%94%20and%20specifically%20of%20Pew's%20role%20in%20perpetuating%20what%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffamilyinequality.wordpress.com%2F2023%2F06%2F07%2Fpew-takes-welcome-steps-to-wean-off-fake-generations-and-some-new-research%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20views%20as%3C%2Fa%3E%20one%20of%20pop%20social%20science's%20greatest%20myths.%20In%202021%20he%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fopinions%2F2021%2F07%2F07%2Fgeneration-labels-mean-nothing-retire-them%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWashington%20Post%20op-ed%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffamilyinequality.wordpress.com%2F2021%2F05%2F26%2Fopen-letter-to-the-pew-research-center-on-generation-labels%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopen%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20asking%20that%20the%20think%20tank%20%26quot%3Bdo%20the%20right%20thing%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bhelp%20put%20an%20end%20to%20the%20use%20of%20arbitrary%20and%20misleading%20'generation'%20labels%20and%20names.%26quot%3B%20More%20than%20200%20social%20scientists%20signed%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20circulation%20of%20Cohen's%20letter%20coincided%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hachettebookgroup.com%2Ftitles%2Fbobby-duffy%2Fthe-generation-myth%2F9781541620308%2F%3Flens%3Dbasic-books%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20release%20of%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BThe%20Generation%20Myth.%26quot%3B%20Written%20by%20Bobby%20Duffy%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Policy%20Institute%20at%20King's%20College%20London%2C%20the%20book%20argued%20that%20%26quot%3Bgenerational%20thinking%26quot%3B%20muddied%20the%20factors%20that%20actually%20%3Cem%3Edo%3C%2Fem%3E%20shape%20people's%20views%20and%20behavior%20over%20time.%20Duffy%20grouped%20these%20into%20three%20categories%3A%20%26quot%3Bperiod%20effects%26quot%3B%20(major%2C%20era-defining%20events%20that%20affect%20everyone%2C%20such%20as%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic)%2C%20%26quot%3Blife-cycle%20events%26quot%3B%20(the%20typical%20milestones%20of%20an%20average%20person's%20life%20within%20a%20given%20society%2C%20such%20as%20getting%20married%20or%20having%20kids)%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bcohort%20effects%26quot%3B%20(the%20overlapping%20experiences%20of%20people%20in%20the%20same%20age%20group).%20The%20trouble%20with%20generational%20thinking%2C%20according%20to%20Duffy%2C%20is%20that%20it%20homes%20in%20on%20cohort%20effects%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20other%20key%20mechanisms%20of%20social%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20and%20large%2C%20Cohen%20shares%20Duffy's%20view%20that%20generational%20labels%20make%20it%20tough%20for%20both%20experts%20and%20laypeople%20to%20distinguish%20between%20generational%20traits%20and%20universal%2C%20or%20multifactorial%2C%20occurrences.%20%26quot%3BIf%20an%20event%20comes%20along%20and%20changes%20things%20for%20everybody%20%E2%80%94%20you%20know%2C%20like%20a%20war%2C%20a%20recession%2C%20a%20pandemic%20%E2%80%94%20those%20things%20are%20not%20generational%2C%20and%20the%20changes%20that%20follow%20aren't%20examples%20of%20generational%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20because%20we're%20fixated%20on%20generational%20labels%2C%20we%20might%20assume%20they%20are.%20We%20might%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20kids%20these%20days%20are%20different%2C'%20when%20really%20it's%20that%20%3Cem%3Epeople%3C%2Fem%3E%20these%20days%20are%20different%2C%20and%20kids%20are%20kids.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuffy%2C%20Cohen%2C%20and%20the%20signatories%20of%20Cohen's%20open%20letter%20believe%20that%20the%20crutch%20of%20generational%20labels%20does%20more%20than%20oversimplify%20the%20complexity%20of%20demographic%20diversity.%20By%20creating%20rigid%20boxes%20for%20research%2C%20the%20labels%20stifle%20the%20potential%20for%20scientific%20breakthroughs.%20They%20can%20also%20warp%20data%2C%20generating%20conclusions%20that%20fail%20to%20encapsulate%20the%20full%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20its%20credit%2C%20Pew%20has%20been%20transparent%20in%20acknowledging%20how%20the%20use%20of%20generational%20labels%20may%20have%20tilted%20its%20analyses.%20In%20one%20of%20the%20center's%20recent%20blog%20posts%2C%20researchers%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fdecoded%2F2023%2F05%2F22%2Fassessing-the-effects-of-generation-using-age-period-cohort-analysis%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevisited%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%202017%20report%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2017%2F02%2F13%2Famericans-are-moving-at-historically-low-rates-in-part-because-millennials-are-staying-put%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easserting%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20millennials%20were%20less%20likely%20than%20prior%20generations%20of%20young%20adults%20to%20move%20residences%20within%20the%20next%20year.%20By%20running%20the%20dataset%20through%20a%20new%20statistical%20model%20that%20decoupled%20generation%20from%20age%20and%20period%2C%20the%20researchers%20arrived%20at%20a%20new%20conclusion%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20apparent%20differences%20between%20the%20generations%20are%20better%20explained%20by%20other%20factors%20in%20the%20model%2C%20%3Cem%3Enot%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Egeneration.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20want%20to%20understand%20each%20other%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20can%20categories%20that%20are%20so%20arbitrary%20and%20often%20unscientific%20also%20be%20so%20%3Cem%3Epresent%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20our%20lives%3F%20There's%20a%20simple%20answer%3A%20Despite%20their%20glass-half-empty%20assessments%2C%20generational%20boxes%20seem%20to%20resonate%20with%20people.%20Lindner%2C%20Stelboum%2C%20and%20Hakim%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fosf.io%2Fpreprints%2Fsocarxiv%2Fe2zxr%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20their%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bafter%20decades%20of%20exposure%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bheavily%20marketed%26quot%3B%20generational%20labels%2C%20Americans%20generally%20identified%20with%20the%20categories%20they'd%20been%20slotted%20into.%20This%20particularly%20applied%20to%20people%20born%20in%20the%20center%20of%20their%20generational%20cohorts%3B%20a%20millennial%20born%20between%201986%20and%201990%20would%20feel%20more%20%26quot%3Bmillennial%26quot%3B%20than%20their%20peers%20born%20in%20the%20five%20years%20before%20or%20after%20that%20window.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EIt%20helps%20capture%20societal%20change%20in%20a%20way%20that%20the%20public%20can%20understand%20and%20identify%20with.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20generational%20labels%20can%20offer%20something%20useful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPew%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20believe%20generational%20research%20can%20be%20a%20useful%20tool%20in%20the%20right%20context%2C%26quot%3B%20Parker%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt%20helps%20capture%20societal%20change%20in%20a%20way%20that%20the%20public%20can%20understand%20and%20identify%20with.%20Also%2C%20outside%20of%20the%20commonly%20used%20definitions%20of%20generations%2C%20people%20can%20understand%20at%20a%20very%20basic%20level%20what%20generational%20change%20is%20%E2%80%94%20my%20generation%20is%20different%20from%20my%20parents'%20and%20my%20grandparents'.%20And%20my%20young-adult%20children%20are%20experiencing%20the%20world%20in%20a%20different%20way%20than%20I%20did.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParker%20and%20her%20colleagues%20note%2C%20however%2C%20that%20young%20adults%20have%20%3Cem%3Ealways%3C%2Fem%3E%20faced%20different%20societal%20circumstances%20than%20their%20parents%20did%20at%20the%20same%20age.%20Pew's%20president%2C%20Michael%20Dimock%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F05%2F22%2F5-things-to-keep-in-mind-when-you-hear-about-gen-z-millennials-boomers-and-other-generations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epointed%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20blog%20post%20that%20it's%20always%20been%20common%20for%20elders%20to%20%26quot%3Bexpress%20some%20degree%20of%20concern%20or%20alarm%26quot%3B%20in%20response%20to%20younger%20people's%20departures%20in%20behavior%20from%20the%20norms%20established%20in%20the%20elders'%20coming%20of%20age.%20There's%20a%20reason%20the%20%26quot%3Bkids%20these%20days%26quot%3B%20trope%20is%2C%20well%2C%20a%20trope.%20Whatever%20generational%20labels%20the%20future%20brings%2C%20it%20seems%20fated%20that%20the%20senior%20citizens%20of%202123%20will%20fixate%20on%20the%20supposed%20character%20deficiencies%20of%20their%20younger%20counterparts%20%E2%80%94%20their%20work%20ethic%2C%20perhaps%2C%20or%20their%20self-obsession%20%E2%80%94%20while%20the%20youth%20bemoan%20the%20challenges%20imparted%20by%20their%20elders'%20mistakes.%20The%20more%20things%20change%2C%20the%20more%20they%20stay%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fkelli-maria-korducki%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22d850c5e918ddf2370e95a753ff8ada81%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fkelli-maria-korducki%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EKelli%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Korducki%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20whose%20work%20focuses%20on%20work%2C%20tech%2C%20and%20culture.%20She's%20based%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennial-boomer-gen-x-why-generations-feud-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690367522000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b996e303c40c001a9718e4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fww