_a%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20Earned%20Income%20Tax%20Credit%20reduced%20the%20likelihood%20of%20being%20in%20poverty%2C%20new%20research%20shows.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EChildren%20exposed%20to%20the%20EITC%20at%20early%20ages%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20receive%20public%20assistance%2C%20such%20as%20WIC%2C%20as%20adults.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20EITC%20reaches%20over%2031%20million%20households%20each%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20IRS.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20research%20reveals%20a%20key%20tax%20credit%20is%20helping%20keep%20many%20children%20out%20of%20poverty%20decades%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20%241%2C000%20increase%20in%20children's%20average%20annual%20exposure%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-earned-income-credit%5C%22%3EEarned%20Income%20Tax%20Credit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20gives%20relief%20to%20middle-%20and%20low-%20earning%20taxpayers%2C%20reduced%20the%20likelihood%20of%20being%20in%20poverty%20or%20near-poverty%20as%20an%20adult%20by%207%20percentage%20points%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw31429%2Fw31429.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20new%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research.%20The%20paper%20also%20determined%20a%20reduction%20in%20public%20assistance%20such%20as%20WIC%20in%20adulthood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20this%20is%20a%20powerful%20finding%20because%20it%20suggests%20that%20investing%20in%20children%20today%20can%20have%20long-term%20societal%20benefits%20in%20the%20form%20of%20reducing%20poverty%20and%20public%20assistance%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20Katherine%20Michelmore%2C%20Associate%20Professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan's%20Gerald%20R.%20Ford%20School%20of%20Public%20Policy%20who%20co-authored%20the%20study%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irs.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fon-eitc-awareness-day-irs-and-partners-promote-major-tax-benefit-to-millions-of-low-and-moderate-income-workers%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%25202022%252C%252031%2520million%2520eligible%2CCongress%2520originally%2520approved%2520in%25201975.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20IRS%20notes%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20EITC%20reaches%20over%2031%20million%20households%20yearly%2C%20or%20about%20half%20of%20families%20with%20children.%20Using%20data%20from%20the%20Panel%20Study%20of%20Income%20Dynamics%2C%20the%20authors%20found%20children%20exposed%20to%20the%20EITC%20at%20younger%20ages%20had%20stronger%20outcomes.%20The%20data%20suggests%20the%20effects%20are%20also%20stronger%20for%20Black%20children%20than%20white%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2025%20and%2045%2C%20the%20study%20found%20that%20a%20%241%2C000%20increase%20in%20annual%20exposure%20to%20EITC%20back%20when%20they%20were%20children%20led%20to%20a%204%20percentage%20point%20increase%20in%20employment%2C%20with%20some%20evidence%20pointing%20to%20earnings%20increases%20for%20those%20in%20the%20bottom%20half%20of%20the%20earnings%20distribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20shows%20how%20policies%20that%20help%20keep%20children%20out%20of%20poverty%20can%20have%20benefits%20for%20decades%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20the%20broader%20literature%20on%20the%20EITC%2C%20our%20paper%20shows%20that%20not%20only%20does%20the%20EITC%20reduce%20poverty%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20help%20break%20the%20cycle%20of%20poverty%20by%20reducing%20the%20likelihood%20of%20being%20poor%20as%20an%20adult%20among%20children%20growing%20up%20in%20low-income%20households%2C%26quot%3B%20Michelmore%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20results%20were%20concentrated%20among%20children%20in%20the%20second%20income%20quartile%2C%20which%20has%20an%20average%20family%20income%20of%20%2445%2C000.%20There%20was%20little%20evidence%20of%20the%20EITC%20reducing%20poverty%20among%20children%20who%20grew%20up%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20income%20distribution%2C%20suggesting%20the%20EITC%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20benefit%20those%20experiencing%20deep%20poverty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20EITC%20is%20structured%20such%20that%20people%20start%20out%20eligible%20for%20zero%20benefits%20if%20they%20don't%20work%2C%20and%20as%20they%20earn%20more%20labor%20income%2C%20they%20qualify%20for%20more%20benefits.%20After%20a%20exceeding%20a%20certain%20income%20level%2C%20benefits%20then%20drop.%20How%20the%20tax%20credit%20can%20be%20restructured%20to%20assist%20those%20who%20need%20the%20benefits%20the%20most%2C%20though%2C%20is%20murky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20be%20working%2C%20but%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20working%20too%20much%2C%20because%20you%20essentially%20start%20losing%20some%20of%20the%20maximum%20benefits%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicardo%20McInnis%2C%20assistant%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20California%20State%20University%2C%20Northridge%20who%20led%20the%20study%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BFor%20families%20that%20don't%20really%20have%20an%20attachment%20to%20the%20labor%20market%20or%20have%20a%20weak%20attachment%2C%20they%20are%20not%20going%20to%20be%20earning%20sufficient%20income%20that%20qualifies%20them%20for%20the%20EITC%20that%20could%20potentially%20make%20a%20difference%20in%20their%20kids'%20lives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20IRS%2C%20those%20who%20qualify%20for%20the%20EITC%20must%20make%20less%20than%20%2459%2C187.%20Those%20without%20qualifying%20children%20can%20claim%20the%20EITC%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2025%20and%2064%2C%20and%20those%20filing%20for%20the%20EITC%20can%20claim%20up%20to%20nearly%20%247%2C000%20in%20credits.%20For%20a%20short%20period%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20childless%20qualifiers%20could%20file%20if%20they%20were%20above%2019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChildren%20who%20grow%20up%20in%20poverty%20have%20a%20higher%20chance%20of%20being%20poor%20in%20adulthood%20than%20those%20who%20did%20not%20grow%20up%20in%20poverty%2C%20according%20to%20the%20authors.%20These%20findings%20suggest%2C%20though%2C%20that%20the%20tax%20credit%20improves%20economic%20outcomes%20of%20both%20the%20EITC%20recipients%20and%20their%20children%2C%20as%20the%20authors%20found%20evidence%20that%20these%20effects%20drive%20up%20income%20mobility.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPast%20research%20has%20shown%20that%20previous%20EITC%20expansions%20resulted%20in%20higher%20short-term%20labor%20force%20participation%20for%20single%20mothers%2C%20heightened%20pre-tax%20earnings%2C%20and%20increased%20test%20scores%20and%20college%20enrollment%20for%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearned-income-tax-credit-parents-reduces-child-poverty-irs-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690366501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c0274ebea3440019617c6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearned-income-tax-credit-parents-reduces-child-poverty-irs-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Children%20exposed%20to%20the%20Earned%20Income%20Tax%20Credit%20at%20an%20early%20age%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20in%20poverty%20in%20adulthood%20and%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20employed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40insider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearned-income-tax-credit-parents-reduces-child-poverty-irs-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Betting%20on%20a%20US%20stock-market%20crash%20hasn't%20been%20this%20cheap%20since%202008%2C%20Bank%20of%20America%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222643%5C%