l%20%E2%80%94%20aimed%20to%20help%20educators%20detect%20academic%20cheating%20%E2%80%94%20it%20had%20acknowledged%20that%20%26quot%3Bidentifying%20AI-written%20text%20has%20been%20an%20important%20point%20of%20discussion%20among%20educators%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20AI%20detection%20tools%20have%20limitations%20and%20should%20not%20be%20the%20primary%20basis%20of%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Tan%2C%20a%20lecturer%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20educators%20are%20adapting%20to%20a%20reality%20where%20generative%20AI%20is%20widely%20available.%26quot%3BMany%20of%20the%20reasons%20why%20students%20might%20use%20AI%20tools%20%E2%80%94like%20stress%20and%20wanting%20a%20shortcut%2C%20not%20seeing%20the%20value%20of%20their%20education%20%E2%80%94%20are%20not%20issues%20that%20I%20can%20solve%20on%20my%20own%20as%20an%20individual%20educator.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20just%20OpenAI's%20detection%20tool%20that's%20throwing%20up%20accuracy%20red%20flags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Turnitin%20%E2%80%94%20a%20plagiarism-checker%20software%20used%20by%20schools%20%E2%80%94%20said%20the%20company's%20new%20tool%20which%20%26quot%3Bdetects%20similarities%20to%20AI%20writing%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.turnitin.com%2Fpress%2Fturnitin-ai-detection-feature-reviews-more-than-65-million-papers%5C%22%3Ehas%20reviewed%20over%2065%20million%20papers%20since%20its%20launch%20in%20April%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20when%20the%20Washington%20Post%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2023%2F04%2F01%2Fchatgpt-cheating-detection-turnitin%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etested%20Turnitin's%20accuracy%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20publication%20found%20the%20software%20incorrectly%20identified%20over%20half%20of%20the%20text%20fed%20into%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20outlets%2C%20like%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C