0seen%20an%20impasse%20since%20the%20monsoon%20session%20began%2C%20with%20opposition%20parties%20insisting%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%20talk%20about%20the%20serious%20ethnic%20conflict%20in%20Manipur%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20house%20and%20allow%20for%20an%20open%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Congress%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20recently%20announced%20INDIA%20alliance%20of%2026%20opposition%20parties%2C%20the%20BRS%20is%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20has%20a%20clear%20majority%20in%20parliament%2C%20so%20the%20opposition%20cannot%20be%20hoping%20to%20win%20the%20motion.%20So%20what%20is%20the%20agenda%20behind%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20breaks%20down%20how%20the%20opposition%20may%20be%20trying%20to%20make%20some%20valuable%20points%20by%20filing%20a%20no-confidence%20motion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20It%20helps%20establish%20the%20fact%20that%20governments%20come%20and%20go%20and%20are%20accountable.%20There%20is%20nothing%20%E2%80%98perpetual%E2%80%99%20or%20forever%20about%20any%20government%2C%20even%20if%20it%20has%20won%20a%20majority%2C%20twice%2C%20running.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20The%20prime%20minister%20does%20not%20address%20Parliament%20and%20frequently%20picks%20%E2%80%98address%20to%20the%20nation%E2%80%99%20modes%2C%20like%20YouTube%20or%20his%20own%20social%20media%20channels%20%E2%80%93%20or%20outside%20Parliament%20%E2%80%93%20as%20stages%20for%20policy%20or%20other%20announcements.%20The%20%E2%80%98temple%20of%20democracy%E2%80%99%20is%20spoken%20of%20and%20worshipped%2C%20but%20its%20value%20as%20an%20institution%20that%20can%20be%20a%20check%20on%20the%20Executive%20is%20under%20serious%20questioning.%20Global%20Indices%20on%20Democracy%20whether%20V-Dem%2C%20Freedom%20House%20or%20International%20IDEA%20have%20recorded%20the%20decline%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Parliament%20as%20a%20check%20on%20government.%20A%20motion%20like%20this%2C%20how%20it%20is%20handled%2C%20draws%20attention%20to%20the%20institution%20and%20its%20ways%20and%20forces%20the%20ruling%20party%20to%20be%20careful%20about%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20There%20is%20a%20drive%20to%20establish%20which%20opposition%20party%20is%20really%20the%20one%20which%20is%20anti%20BJP.%20There%20is%20a%20vast%20line%20of%20%E2%80%98middlers%E2%80%99%2C%20parties%20like%20BRS%2C%20YSRCP%2C%20BJD%20and%20numerous%20others%2C%20not%20amongst%20the%20new%20NDA%20(38)%20or%20INDIA%20(26)%20parties%20that%20are%20then%20forced%20to%20take%20a%20call%20and%20show%20their%20cards.%20This%20helps%20draw%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20Within%20INDIA%20too%2C%20there%20is%20Little%20INDIA%2C%20some%20doubts%20and%20concerns%20about%20certain%20parties%2C%20about%20where%20they%20really%20stand.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20sizeable%20faction%20of%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20is%20now%20with%20the%20BJP%20government%20in%20Maharashtra%20and%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20interest%20in%20which%20way%20things%20will%20go.%20This%20helps%20establish%20who%20is%20standing%20where.%20As%20whatever%20may%20be%20the%20chances%20of%20winning%20it%2C%20no%20government%20can%20take%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%20non-seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690353017000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16103200%2FGlimpses_of_the_new_Parliament_Building_in_New_Delhi_2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-a-no-confidence-motion-now-four-tactical-advantages-the-opposition-might-be-aiming-for%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20is%20no%20expectation%20amongst%20the%20opposition%20parties%20that%20it%20will%20be%20won.%20The%20difference%20is%20clear.%20BJP%20commands%20a%20majority%20of%20its%20own%2C%20well%20clear%20of%20the%20272%20mark%20(let%20alone%20majority%20amongst%20those%20present%20and%20voting).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-a-no-confidence-motion-now-four-tactical-advantages-the-opposition-might-be-aiming-for%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MS%20Dhoni%20to%20act%20in%20films%3F%20Sakshi%20reacts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690352554000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102128785%2Cimgsize-37328.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fms-dhoni-is-open-to-acting-in-films-reveals-his-wife-sakshi-dhoni-hes-not-camera-shy%2Farticleshow%2F102128785.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102128785.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EMahendra%20Singh%20Dhoni%20is%20open%20to%20acting%20in%20films%2C%20according%20to%20his%20wife%2C%20Sakshi%20Dhoni.%20The%20couple%20has%20recently%20ventured%20into%20film%20production%20with%20their%20company%20Dhoni%20Entertainment.%20If%20there%20is%20a%20good%20opportunity%2C%20Dhoni%20may%20consider%20acting%20in%20an%20action%20film%2C%20as%20he%20is%20not%20camera-shy%20and%20has%20acted%20in%20advertisements%20before.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fms-dhoni-is-open-to-acting-in-films-reveals-his-wife-sakshi-dhoni-hes-not-camera-shy%2Farticleshow%2F102128785.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Union%20Govt%20Moves%20SC%20to%20Extend%20ED%20Director%20S.K.%20Mishra's%20Tenure%20Days%20After%20'Illegal'%20Ruling%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F11%2F15174623%2FSKMishra_EDdirector_141120_1200.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%20has%20moved%20Supreme%20Court%20seeking%20the%20extension%20of%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%E2%80%99s%20chief%2C%20S.K.%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20in%20office%2C%20days%20after%20the%20apex%20court%20ruled%20that%20earlier%20extensions%20given%20to%20him%20had%20been%20illegal%20and%20that%20he%20cannot%20be%20allowed%20to%20stay%20on%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20through%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FLiveLawIndia%2Fstatus%2F1684070130219884545%5C%22%3Etweet%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20told%20the%20court%20today%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20is%20filing%20an%20application%20with%20regards%20to%20the%20recent%20judgment%20on%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20tenure.%20Requesting%20this%20application%20to%20be%20listed%20in%20front%20of%20the%20court%20before%20Friday%2C%20July%2028%2C%20SG%20Mehta%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20making%20some%20prayer%20that%20will%20have%20to%20persuade%20this%20court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20agreed%20to%20list%20it%20at%203.30%20pm%20tomorrow%2C%20July%2027.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMishra%E2%80%99s%20term%20will%20end%20on%20July%2031.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%20July%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-enforcement-directorate-sk-mishra-extensions-illegal%5C%22%3Eheld%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20extensions%20given%20to%20Mishra%20after%20its%20own%20earlier%20order%20barring%20further%20extensions%20were%20invalid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20three-judge%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20Vikram%20Nath%20and%20Sanjay%20Karol%20had%20allowed%20Mishra%20to%20continue%20in%20his%20post%20till%20July%2031.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20because%20the%20Union%20government%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fenforcement-directorate-sanjay-mishra-supreme-court-fatf%5C%22%3Esaid%20that%20the%20international%20terror%20financing%20watchdog%20FATF%E2%80%99s%20peer%20review%20process%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20best%20overseen%20by%20Mishra.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsk-mishra-enforcement-directorate-fatf-evaluation%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20how%20a%20country%20is%20judged%20on%20at%20least%2040%20parameters%20by%20the%20FATF%20and%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%E2%80%99s%20remit%20of%20money%20laundering%20and%20terror%20financing%20is%20just%20one%20of%20those%2040.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20July%20order%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20also%2C%20however%2C%20noted%20that%20it%20had%20little%20power%20over%20amendments%20to%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20Act%20and%20Delhi%20Special%20Police%20Establishment%20Act.%20These%20were%20brought%20through%20ordinances%20by%20the%20government%20and%20allowed%20ED%20and%20CBI%20chiefs%E2%80%99%20tenures%20to%20be%20extended%20by%20up%20to%20three%20years%20after%20the%20mandated%20term%20of%20two%20years.%20Notably%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20brought%20these%20changes%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20already%20ordered%20it%20to%20not%20give%20the%20ED%20chief%20further%20extensions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20line%20taken%20by%20the%20SC%20had%20faced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fsuprem-court-enforcement-directorate-sk-mishra-amit-shah-editorials%5C%22%3Ecriticism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20newspaper%20editorials%20asking%20why%20the%20court%20was%20not%20exercising%20its%20power%20of%20judicial%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20SC%E2%80%99s%20verdict%2C%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Famit-shah-opposition-supreme-court-delusional-ed-congress-tmc%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20a%20sign%20of%20victory.%20Shah%20had%20also%20claimed%20that%20the%20institution%20of%20the%20ED%20%E2%80%9Crises%20beyond%20any%20one%20individual%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20a%20notion%20that%20the%20current%20application%20filed%20by%20his%20government%20would%20go%20against.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPowers%20of%20the%20ED%20to%20strike%20at%20those%20who%20are%20corrupt%20and%20on%20the%20wrong%20side%20of%20the%20law%20remain%20the%20same.%20ED%20is%20an%20institution%20which%20rises%20beyond%20any%20one%20individual%20and%20is%20focused%20on%20achieving%20its%20core%20objective%20%E2%80%93%20i.e.%20to%20investigate%20offences%20of%20money%20laundering%20and%20violations%20of%20foreign%20exchange%20laws%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shah%20had%20said%20after%20the%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%2C%20the%20partisan%20role%20of%20central%20investigative%20agencies%20like%20the%20ED%20and%20the%20CBI%20have%20come%20under%20the%20scanner%2C%20with%20opposition%20leaders%20almost%20exclusively%20targeted%20by%20these%20two%20bodies.%20Cases%20registered%20against%20such%20leaders%20also%20tend%20to%20fall%20by%20the%20wayside%20when%20politicians%20jump%20ship%20and%20join%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690351957000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F11%2F15174623%2FSKMishra_EDdirector_141120_1200.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-enforcement-directorate-government-mishra-extension-again%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20three-judge%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.R.%20Gavai%2C%20Vikram%20Nath%20and%20Sanjay%20Karol%20had%20earlier%20in%20July%20allowed%20Mishra%20to%20continue%20in%20his%20post%20till%20July%2031.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-enforcement-directorate-government-mishra-extension-again%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Impose%20Conditions%20on%20Recipients%20of%20Govt%20Honours%20to%20Prevent%20'Award%20Wapsi'%3A%20Parliamentary%20Panel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F06%2Fdelhi.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20parliamentary%20committee%20has%20recommended%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20put%20a%20system%20in%20place%20to%20take%20prior%20undertakings%20from%20shortlisted%20candidates%20for%20government%20awards%20to%20avoid%20an%20%E2%80%98award-wapsi-like%20situation%E2%80%99%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20system%20may%20be%20put%20in%20place%20where%20an%20undertaking%20is%20taken%20from%20the%20proposed%20awardee%20citing%20acceptance%20of%20the%20award%20and%20that%20the%20awardees%20cannot%20dishonor%20the%20award%20at%20any%20point%20of%20time%20in%20future%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0stated%20a%20report%20tabled%20in%20parliament%20by%20the%20parliamentary%20committee%20on%20transport%2C%20tourism%2C%20and%20culture%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fparliamentary-committee-recommends-prior-undertakings-from-recipients-cultural-institutions-academies-2411480-2023-07-25%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20report%20by%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tribuneindia.com%2Fnews%2Fnation%2Fwary-of-award-wapsi-parliamentary-committee-wants-undertaking-from-recipients-529065%3F_gl%3D1*d6iqub*_ga*OUJWNVBJbWNyV25nSlBsSy1ONHk2QkVDS3lXaXVOWi1mMzFhdFdUdE5mVHdqZ3FQd0xqREZpMjJnU0VidnA0dg%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%20Tribune%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20further%20quoted%20the%20committee%20as%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CAwards%20may%20not%20be%20given%20without%20such%20an%20undertaking.%20In%20the%20event%20that%20the%20awards%20are%20returned%2C%20the%20awardee%20shall%20not%20be%20considered%20for%20such%20an%20award%20in%20the%20future.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20termed%20the%20act%20of%20returning%20awards%20in%20protest%20against%20political%20issues%20%E2%80%9Cdisgraceful%20to%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%20While%20noting%20that%20political%20issues%20are%20outside%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20cultural%20realms%2C%20returning%20awards%2C%20according%20to%20the%20committee%2C%20would%20impact%20the%20overall%20prestige%20and%20reputation%20of%20the%20awards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20parliamentary%20panel%20argued%20that%20it%20is%20important%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Creturn%20of%20the%20award%20is%20not%20used%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20political%20protest%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Federal%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthefederal.com%2Fstates%2Fsouth%2Fkarnataka%2Faward-wapsi-clause-proposal-shocks-literary-cultural-fraternity-in-karnataka%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20report%20is%20titled%20%3Cem%3EFunctioning%20of%20National%20Akademies%20and%20Other%20Cultural%20Institutions%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20from%20September%202015%2C%20eminent%20writers%2C%20filmmakers%2C%20and%20other%20prominent%20personalities%20returned%20awards%20given%20to%20them%20by%20the%20government%20to%20protest%20against%20the%20targeting%20of%20minorities%20and%20the%20spate%20of%20communal%20violence%20under%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government.%20Many%20prominent%20personalities%20also%20returned%20the%20honours%20bestowed%20on%20them%20by%20the%20government%20in%20protest%20specifically%20against%20the%20murders%20of%20rationalists%20like%20M.M.%20Kalburgi%2C%20Govind%20Pansare%20and%20Narendra%20Dabholkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20them%20returned%20the%20plaque%20and%20others%20sent%20back%20the%20cheques%20of%20amounts%20they%20received%20as%20part%20of%20the%20award.%20The%20committee%20said%20it%20was%20informed%20by%20the%20Sahitya%20Akademi%20that%20it%20does%20not%20have%20any%20system%20for%20taking%20back%20the%20award.%20Therefore%2C%20cheques%20were%20not%20deposited%2C%20and%20there%20was%20no%20instance%20of%20%E2%80%9Caward%20wapsi%E2%80%9D%20after%202015%2C%20the%20committee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20specifically%20noted%20that%2039%20recipients%20of%20the%20Sahitya%20Akademi%20Awards%20returned%20their%20awards%20in%202015%20to%20protest%20the%20murder%20of%20Kalburgi.%C2%A0%20The%20Committee%20said%20some%20of%20the%20awardees%20who%20had%20returned%20their%20awards%20continued%20their%20association%20with%20the%20Akademi%2C%20serving%20either%20on%20the%20jury%20or%20participating%20in%20the%20Akademi%E2%80%99s%20programmes.%20It%20questioned%20the%20re-engagement%20of%20such%20awardees%20who%20joined%20the%20Akademi%20%E2%80%9Cafter%20insulting%20it%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Federal%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20quoted%20several%20writers%2C%20filmmakers%2C%20academicians%2C%20theatre%2C%20and%20folk%20personalities%20of%20Karnataka%20who%20termed%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20panel%20as%20%E2%80%9Canti-democratic%2C%20an%20assault%20on%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20an%20attempt%20to%20curtail%20the%20freedom%20to%20protest%20in%20any%20form%20granted%20by%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAwards%20are%20primarily%20being%20conferred%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20achievement%20of%20personality%20in%20the%20specified%20field%20of%20art.%20The%20selection%20of%20the%20person%20is%20based%20on%20recommendation%20of%20a%20jury%20or%20selection%20committee.%20It%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20both%20the%20government%20and%20cultural%20institution%20not%20to%20humiliate%20personalities%20they%20chose%20for%20the%20award%20by%20imposing%20conditions.%20Karnataka%20has%20a%20history%20of%20respecting%20the%20creative%20freedom%20of%20cultural%20personalities%20and%20protecting%20them%20from%20any%20autocratic%20and%20undemocratic%20political%20dispensation%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20noted%20writer%20and%20cultural%20critic%20Baraguru%20Ramachandrappa.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690351820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F06%2Fdelhi.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fimpose-conditions-on-recipients-of-govt-honours-to-prevent-award-wapsi-parliamentary-panel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20parliamentary%20committee%20on%20transport%2C%20tourism%2C%20and%20culture%20said%20the%20government%20must%20ensure%20that%20the%20'return%20of%20the%20award%20is%20not%20used%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20political%20protest'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fimpose-conditions-on-recipients-of-govt-honours-to-prevent-award-wapsi-parliamentary-panel%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prakash%20Jha's%20father%20Tejnath%20passes%20away%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690351533000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102128070%2Cimgsize-98141.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Ftejnath-jha-father-of-producer-director-prakash-jha-passes-away-in-patna%2Farticleshow%2F102128113.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102128113.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ETejnath%20Jha%2C%20father%20of%20producer-director%20Prakash%20Jha%20has%20passed%20away%20in%20Patna.%20He%20was%2095%20years%20old.%20According%20to%20reports%2C%20he%20had%20been%20unwell%20for%20the%20last%20few%20days%20and%20died%20of%20old%20age%20related%20complications%20at%20his%20residence.%20Prakash%20Jan%20is%20known%20for%20movies%20like%20Gangaajal%2C%20Apaharan%2C%20Satyagraha%2C%20Rajneeti%20etc%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Ftejnath-jha-father-of-producer-director-prakash-jha-passes-away-in-patna%2Farticleshow%2F102128113.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Unlimited%20Powers%20to%20Harass'%3A%20Ex%20Civil%20Servants%20Criticise%20Modi%20Govt's%20Changes%20to%20Service%20Rules%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26104436%2Fdaniel-alvasd-NItozEcUPrw-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20group%20of%2094%20former%20civil%20servants%20have%20released%20a%20statement%20expressing%20concerns%20over%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20changes%20to%20the%20All%20India%20Service%20Rules.%20These%20rules%2C%20the%20statement%20says%2C%20will%20make%20it%20impossible%20for%20public%20servants%20to%20express%20their%20opinions%20on%20matters%20of%20national%20importance.%20If%20they%20do%20not%20comply%2C%20their%20pensions%20may%20be%20revoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20released%20under%20the%20umbrella%20of%20the%20Constitutional%20Conduct%20Group%2C%20the%20former%20civil%20servants%20have%20said%20that%20the%20proposed%20changes%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20be%20violative%20of%20Article%2051A%20of%20the%20Constitution%20which%20enjoins%20upon%20all%20citizens%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Echerish%20and%20follow%20the%20noble%20ideals%20that%20inspired%20the%20national%20struggle%20for%20freedom%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%20The%20right%20to%20criticise%20the%20government%20in%20power%20is%20part%20of%20these%20ideals%20and%20cannot%20be%20termed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmisconduct%E2%80%9D%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CConsidering%20the%20severe%20penalties%20prescribed%20for%20misconduct%2C%20it%20is%20legally%20incumbent%20on%20the%20union%20government%20to%20have%20provided%20an%20exhaustive%20definition%20of%20the%20term.%20By%20leaving%20this%20deliberately%20vague%2C%20ambiguous%20and%20amorphous%2C%20the%20union%20government%20has%20armed%20itself%20with%20unlimited%20powers%20to%20harass%20and%20persecute%20any%20pensioner%20whose%20action%20is%20not%20to%20its%20liking%2C%20whether%20it%20be%C2%A0%20an%20article%2C%20an%20interview%2C%20participation%20in%20a%20protest%20march%20or%20seminar%2C%20or%20any%20form%20of%20criticism%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20statement%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitutional%20Conduct%20Group%2C%20a%20collective%20of%20former%20civil%20servants%2C%20has%20noted%20with%20concern%20the%20recent%20amendments%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Personnel%2C%20Public%20Grievances%20and%20Pensioners%2C%20Govt.%20of%20India%2C%20to%20the%20All%20India%20Services%20(Death%20cum%20Retirement%20Benefits)%20Rules%201958%20(hereinafter%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20Rules).%20Through%20a%20notification%20dated%206.7.2023%2C%20these%20amendments%20have%2C%20%3Cem%3Einter%20alia%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20sought%20to%20impose%20a%20complete%20ban%20on%20the%20right%20of%20retired%20civil%20servants%20to%20comment%20on%20public%20matters%2C%20by%20threatening%20them%20with%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20their%20pensions.%20This%20would%20be%20violative%20of%20Article%2051A%20of%20the%20Constitution%20which%20enjoins%20upon%20all%20citizens%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Echerish%20and%20follow%20the%20noble%20ideals%20that%20inspired%20the%20national%20struggle%20for%20freedom%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%20The%20right%20to%20criticise%20the%20government%20in%20power%20is%20part%20of%20these%20ideals%20and%20cannot%20be%20termed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmisconduct%E2%80%9D%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20original%20Rules%20of%201958%20(as%20amended%20from%20time%20to%20time)%20did%20contain%20a%20provision%20in%20Rule%203%20that%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Efuture%20good%20conduct%20shall%20be%20an%20implied%20condition%20of%20every%20grant%20of%20pension%20and%20its%20continuation%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20pension%20could%20be%20withheld%20or%20withdrawn%2C%20in%20part%20or%20in%20full%2C%20if%20the%20pensioner%20is%20convicted%20of%20a%20serious%20crime%20or%20is%20held%20to%20be%20guilty%20of%20grave%20misconduct.%20However%2C%20such%20action%20could%20only%20be%20taken%20by%20the%20union%20government%20on%20a%20reference%20from%20the%20state%20government%20(the%20cadre%20to%20which%20the%20officer%20belonged).%20But%20now%2C%20Rule%203%20has%20been%20amended%20to%20provide%20that%20such%20punitive%20action%20can%20be%20taken%20by%20the%20union%20government%20%E2%80%9C%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Eeither%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20on%20a%20reference%20from%20the%20state%20government%20concerned%20%3Cstrong%3Eor%20otherwise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%20This%2C%20we%20feel%2C%20violates%20the%20principles%20of%20federalism%20and%20confers%20draconian%20powers%20of%20oversight%20and%20overrule%20on%20the%20union%20government%20which%20is%20not%20in%20conformity%20with%20the%20duality%20of%20control%20envisaged%20in%20the%20All%20India%20Services%20structure.%20It%20will%20further%20expose%20officers%20in%20opposition%20ruled%20states%20to%20intimidation%20by%20the%20party%20in%20power%20at%20the%20centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20note%20with%20apprehension%20that%20nowhere%20in%20the%20Rules%20has%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20conduct%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cgrave%20misconduct%E2%80%9D%20been%20defined%2C%20other%20than%20in%20sub-rule%208%20of%20Rule%203%20which%20merely%20%E2%80%9Cincludes%E2%80%9D%20disclosure%20of%20any%20information%20covered%20by%20the%20Official%20Secrets%20Act%20as%20a%20grave%20misconduct.%20Other%20than%20this%2C%20however%2C%20the%20Rules%20are%20completely%20silent%20on%20this%20issue%2C%20and%20everything%20is%20left%20to%20the%20decision%20or%20interpretation%20of%20the%20central%20government.%20Considering%20the%20severe%20penalties%20prescribed%20for%20misconduct%2C%20it%20is%20legally%20incumbent%20on%20the%20union%20government%20to%20have%20provided%20an%20exhaustive%20definition%20of%20the%20term.%20By%20leaving%20this%20deliberately%20vague%2C%20ambiguous%20and%20amorphous%2C%20the%20union%20government%20has%20armed%20itself%20with%20unlimited%20powers%20to%20harass%20and%20persecute%20any%20pensioner%20whose%20action%20is%20not%20to%20its%20liking%2C%20whether%20it%20be%C2%A0%20an%20article%2C%20an%20interview%2C%20participation%20in%20a%20protest%20march%20or%20seminar%2C%20or%20any%20form%20of%20criticism.%20In%20effect%2C%20this%20will%20totally%20muzzle%20and%20silence%20anyone%20who%20draws%20a%20pension%20from%20the%20state%2C%20which%20appears%20to%20be%20the%20intention%20behind%20these%20amendments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20withdrawal%2Fwithholding%20of%20pension%20for%20any%20criminal%20conviction%20is%20equally%20pernicious%20and%20untenable%20in%20law%20as%20it%20amounts%20to%20double%20jeopardy%2C%20punishing%20a%20person%20twice%20for%20the%20same%20offence.%20The%20pension%20is%20something%20(s)he%20has%20already%20earned%20by%20dint%20of%20long%20service.%20If%20(s)he%20commits%20a%20crime%2C%20(s)he%20will%20suffer%20the%20consequences%20of%20that%20by%20the%20operation%20of%20that%20criminal%20law%3A%20(s)he%20cannot%20be%20penalised%20a%20second%20time%20for%20the%20same%20offence%20by%20withdrawing%20her%2Fhis%20pension.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20law%20punishes%20the%20perpetrator%20of%20a%20crime%2C%20not%20her%2Fhis%20next%20of%20kin%3B%20by%20withdrawing%2Fwithholding%20her%2Fhis%20pension%20the%20government%20would%20be%20inflicting%20unjustified%20tribulations%20and%20misery%20on%20her%2Fhis%20family%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20both%20the%20original%20and%20the%20amended%20provision%20of%20Rule%203%20(except%20the%20newly%20introduced%20sub-rule%206%20about%20divulging%20secret%20and%20security%20related%20information)%20violate%20multiple%20rulings%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20various%20High%20Courts%20which%20have%2C%20over%20the%20last%2065%20years%2C%20constantly%20held%20that%20pension%20is%20an%20employee%E2%80%99s%20right%20and%20a%20kind%20of%20deferred%20payment%20for%20service%20already%20rendered.%20It%20is%20not%20largesse%20or%20charity%20bestowed%20by%20the%20government%20and%20does%20not%20depend%20upon%20the%20discretion%20of%20the%20government%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E(State%20of%20Punjab%20and%20Another%20vs%20Iqbal%20Singh)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDS%20Nakara%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%20(1983)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20that%20a%20law%20cannot%20discriminate%20between%20the%20same%20class%20of%20people%2C%20and%20that%20all%20statutes%20or%20laws%20must%20have%20some%20rational%20nexus%20with%20the%20object%20of%20the%20law.%20Rule%203%2C%20both%20the%20original%20and%20the%20amended%20versions%2C%20do%20not%20conform%20to%20these%20legal%20requirements.%20Pensioners%20are%20no%20longer%20government%20servants%3A%20they%20are%20free%20citizens%20of%20the%20country%20like%20any%20other%20citizen%2C%20with%20the%20same%20freedom%20of%20expression.%20By%20curbing%20this%20right%20under%20the%20specious%20guise%20of%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20conduct%E2%80%9D%20the%20government%20is%20discriminating%20against%20them%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20also%20violating%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Furthermore%2C%20what%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cobject%E2%80%9D%20of%20this%20rule%2C%20if%20not%20to%20silence%20any%20form%20of%20criticism%20of%20the%20government%3F%20This%20cannot%20be%20held%20to%20be%20rational%2C%20reasonable%20or%20based%20on%20some%20valid%20principle%2C%20as%20is%20required%20in%20another%20judgment%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E(Ramana%20Dayaram%20Shetty%20vs%20The%20Airport%20Authority%20of%20India%20and%20Others)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERule%203%20has%20become%20obsolete%3A%20it%20is%20a%20legal%20anachronism%20which%20also%20militates%20against%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20dissent.%20It%20makes%20pensioners%20bonded%20labourers%20for%20life%2C%20a%20separate-and%20inferior-class%20of%20citizens%20who%20do%20not%20enjoy%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression.%20It%20further%20seeks%20to%20impose%20the%20Conduct%20Rules%20(which%20apply%20only%20to%20those%20in%20service%20of%20the%20government)%20on%20pensioners%20through%20the%20back%20door%2C%20which%20is%20abhorrent%20in%20law%2C%20as%20the%20latter%20are%20no%20longer%20in%20service.%20They%20are%20free%20citizens%20and%20there%20exists%20no%20employer-employee%20relationship%20between%20them%20and%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERules%20governing%20conditions%20of%20service%20need%20to%20be%20dynamic%20and%20in%20sync%20with%20the%20changes%20in%20interpretation%20of%20laws%2C%20the%20evolution%20of%20jurisprudence%20on%20rights%20and%20freedoms%2C%20the%20development%20of%20the%20concepts%20of%20democracy%20and%20an%20open%20society.%20Rule%203%20fails%20to%20do%20so%2C%20is%20stuck%20in%20a%20time%20warp%20and%20needs%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitutional%20Conduct%20Group%20urges%20the%20governments%20in%20the%20states%20and%20the%20union%20government%20to%20review%20this%20rule%20with%20a%20view%20to%20abolishing%20it%2C%20and%20not%20to%20further%20build%20upon%20it.%20In%20the%20interim%20we%20further%20request%20the%20union%20government%20to%20hold%20in%20abeyance%20these%20amendments%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20federalism%2C%20fair%20play%2C%20equality%20of%20citizens%2C%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20a%20vibrant%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESATYAMEVA%20JAYATE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConstitutional%20Conduct%20Group%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E(94%20signatories)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%20width%3D%5C%22614%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2256%5C%22%3E1.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22123%5C%22%3EAnita%20Agnihotri%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2295%5C%22%3EIAS%20(Retd.)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22340%5C%22%3EFormer%20Secretary%2C%20Department%20of%20Social%20Justice%20Empowerment%2C