ge%20had%20worsened%20because%20Western%20media%20had%20never%20accepted%20the%20Chinese%20political%20system%20or%20its%20economic%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQin%E2%80%99s%20closeness%20with%20Xi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQin%20rapidly%20rose%20within%20the%20Communist%20Party%20hierarchy%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20say%20the%20rise%20was%20due%20to%20his%20closeness%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fxi-jinping%2Ft-17449321%5C%22%3EPresident%20Xi%20Jinping.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%202014%20to%202017%2C%20Qin%20worked%20as%20head%20of%20the%20foreign%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20diplomatic%20protocol%20department.%20During%20this%20stint%2C%20he%20had%20regular%20contact%20with%20Xi%20and%20organized%20the%20president%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20trips.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQin%20was%20viewed%20as%20Xi%E2%80%99s%20prot%C3%A9g%C3%A9%20and%20appointed%20as%20a%20vice-minister%20of%20foreign%20affairs%2C%20a%20role%20he%20held%C2%A0between%202018%20and%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfterward%2C%20he%20was%20sent%20to%20Washington%20as%20China%E2%80%99s%C2%A0ambassador%20to%20the%20United%20States%2C%20where%20he%20gained%20prominence%20through%20public%20and%20media%20appearances%C2%A0in%20which%20he%20stridently%20defended%20Chinese%20geopolitical%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20as%20ambassador%2C%20he%20was%20less%20confrontational%20than%20he%20had%20been%20previously%20in%20Beijing.%C2%A0In%20that%20role%2C%20he%20was%20charged%20with%C2%A0putting%20the%20relationship%20between%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20two%20largest%20economies%20back%20on%20track.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQin%E2%80%99s%20disappearance%20%E2%80%98highly%20troublesome%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20experiences%20culminated%20in%20Qin%E2%80%99s%20most%20recent%20position%3A%20In%20December%202022%2C%20at%20the%C2%A0relatively%20young%20age%20of%2057%2C%20he%20became%20one%20of%20the%20youngest%20foreign%20ministers%20in%20Chinese%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQin%20also%20gained%20entry%20into%20the%20Communist%20Party%E2%80%99s%20central%20committee%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20since%20Qin%20disappeared%20from%20public%20view%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fwhat-happened-to-chinas-missing-foreign-minister%2Fa-66294826%5C%22%3Emystery%20of%20his%20whereabouts%20and%20fate%20have%20sparked%20fevered%20speculation%3C%2Fa%3E%20both%20inside%20and%20outside%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWu%20Qiang%2C%20an%20independent%20academic%20and%20political%20commentator%20in%20China%2C%20told%20DW%C2%A0last%20week%20that%20the%20episode%20speaks%20volumes%20about%20the%20current%20state%20of%20Xi%E2%80%99s%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20abrupt%20disappearance%20of%20Qin%20%E2%80%9Cis%20highly%20troublesome%E2%80%9D%20since%20it%20indicates%20that%20Beijing%20may%20be%20moving%20closer%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmystical%20and%20unpredictable%E2%80%9D%20form%20of%20autocratic%20leadership%2C%20he%20stressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fwho-is-qin-gang-chinas-sacked-foreign-minister%2Fa-66345677%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690347732000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26094304%2FUntitled-design-8.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwho-is-qin-gang-chinas-sacked-foreign-minister%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China%20has%20sacked%20Qin%20Gang%20as%20foreign%20minister%20and%20appointed%20his%20predecessor%2C%20Wang%20Yi%2C%20to%20the%20post.%20Qin%20has%20not%20been%20seen%20in%20public%20since%20June%2025%2C%20triggering%20widespread%20speculation%20about%20his%20whereabouts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonica